==Portuguese==
===Etymology===
Uncertain. If the element *''bac-'' is a metathesis of *''kab-'' (cf. French ''[[cabillaud]]'' and German ''[[Kabeljau]]'' from Dutch (''[[kabeljauw]]''), then the original form of the word could have been *''cabalhau'', maybe meaning "large-headed fish".
===Pronunciation===
*IPA: /baka'ʎaw/
===Noun===
